article.description: Travon Baker scored 18 points, including eight in a row in a key stretch late, and seventh-seeded Northern Illinois beat No. 10 seed Western Michigan 56-50 in a Mid-American Conference tournament
article.headline: Northern Illinois eliminates Western Michigan in MAC 56-50
article.linkText: Northern Illinois eliminates Western Michigan in MAC 56-50
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. -- Travon Baker scored 18 points, including eight in a row in a key stretch late, and seventh-seeded Northern Illinois beat No. 10 seed Western Michigan 56-50 in a Mid-American Conference tournament first round matchup on Monday night. The Huskies (21-11) will play second-seeded Ohio (20-10) in the quarterfinals Thursday. The teams split two games in the regular season. A close game throughout, a 3-point play by Western Michigan's Tucker Haymond tied it at 42 with 5:35 to go. Baker drilled 3-pointers on the next two possessions, and then hit a pair of free throws, and the Huskies didn't trail again. Western Michigan got within two points twice late, but Northern Illinois made 7 of 8 free throws in the last 33 seconds. Levi Bradley had 13 points with a career-high 12 rebounds and Aaric Armstead scored 12 for NIU. Haymond led Western Michigan (13-19) with 17 points. The Broncos were just 2 of 12 from beyond the arc.
